ml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"pop-ups";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"social media";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Startup pop-ups";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:12;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"time-based";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://www.jigoshop.com/?p=50407";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:623:"<p>Pop-ups, while annoying to site visitors, can be very helpful to your Jigoshop eCommerce site. A pop-up does as the name implies; it pops up on a web page at some point during your interaction on the site. They briefly <a class="read-more" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/use-pop-ads-bolster-jigoshop-ecommerce-business/">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/use-pop-ads-bolster-jigoshop-ecommerce-business/">Use Pop-Up Ads to Bolster Your  Jigoshop eCommerce Business</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Michael Stone";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5129:"<p>Pop-ups, while annoying to site visitors, can be very helpful to your Jigoshop eCommerce site. A pop-up does as the name implies; it pops up on a web page at some point during your interaction on the site. They briefly interrupt your surfing experience and force you to either wait until a set time passes for you to close it or just allow you to close it at any time.</p>\n<p>Although pop-ups can be annoying to customers, they can be a great help to your business.</p>\n<h2>What Is the Purpose of a Pop-up?</h2>\n<p>A pop-ups goal is to provide a call to action. It can be any action that you would like. Things such as a sale going on, an upcoming event, or simply to collect email addresses for your newsletter.</p>\n<p>Most of the time, the purpose of a pop-up is to collect customer email addresses. In fact, studies show that this usage is very successful.</p>\n<p>In one such case, <a href="https://blog.aweber.com/email-marketing/easy-secret-more-subscribers.htm" target="_blank">a blogger with an Etsy shop decided to utilize a pop-up and a newsletter signup on the sidebar of her site</a>. Eight months later she analyzed her results to see that the results differed significantly between the pop-up and sidebar. The subscription rate for the sidebar was 0.4% while the subscription price for the pop up was 5.5% in comparison. That is a whopping 1,375% more sign-ups than the sidebar received.</p>\n<h2>Why Collect Email Addresses As Opposed to Followers on Social Media?</h2>\n<p>Having customers falling on social media is always good. However, having permission to send them emails is much better.</p>\n<p>With social media, you have to rely on a customer either going directly to your social media page or haphazardly scrolling by to see your content.</p>\n<p>On the flipside, having permission to email customers allows you to communicate with your client one-on-one in a personal online environment. Another advantage email has over social media is that there are less possible distractions drawing a customer away from your content.</p>\n<h2>Other Uses of Pop-Ups</h2>\n<p>Email is the primary use of a pop-up advertisement, but there are others.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Answering a question before it asked.</li>\n<li>Encouraging a visitor to view a particular piece of content on your site.</li>\n<li>Announce discount.</li>\n<li>Share a new product.</li>\n<li>Gain customer insight.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Bad Aspects of Pop-Ups?</h2>\n<p>The fact that pop-ups work for collecting email addresses or relating information to customers does not necessarily negate the bad aspects of using them.</p>\n<p>Here are some possible disadvantages:</p>\n<h3>Disadvantages</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Many visitors do not like pop-ups and will even exit your site immediately when they see one.</li>\n<li>Pop-ups can slow down your website&#8217;s load time, especially pop-ups that contain scripts. Slow load times can sometimes lead to a high bounce rate.</li>\n<li>In some cases, if a pop-up appears at the wrong time can be annoying and distracting to your site visitors.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Different Types of Pop-Ups</strong></h2>\n<p>Various types of pop-ups exist. Here are a few:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Start-up Pop-Ups</strong> – These pop-ups appear within seconds of a person visiting your site.</li>\n<li><strong>Time-Based </strong>– These pop-up ads appear after a set amount of time and usually work better if they are set to 60 seconds or more.</li>\n<li><strong>Mouseover Pop-Up </strong>– Pop-ups that are configured to trigger when you are mouse hovers over a particular item of the page. The item could be as simple as text.</li>\n<li><strong>Scroll-based </strong>– scroll base pop-ups appear when a user scrolls to a particular point on the page. A good place to use this method of pop-up is in a blog post.</li>\n<li><strong>Floating Pop-Up</strong> – This pop-up does not allow a user to continue unless they complete a particular action or choose to opt out.</li>\n<li><strong>Pop-Out</strong> – This particular pop-up appears to the side of the browser. They are great because they allow a customer to continue browsing unimpeded.</li>\n<li><strong>Exit-Intent </strong>– a pop-up that uses cursor tracking to determine when someone is about to leave your site to trigger a pop-up. Usually, this is a last-ditch effort to get an email newsletter often or offer a discount.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\n<p>Pop-ups can be a great addition to your Jigoshop eCommerce websites marketing plan. However, there are disadvantages. Some customers may choose to exit your site as soon as they see a pop-up and some pop-ups may slow down your sites rendering. Both of these issues can lead to high bounce rates.</p>\n<p>With that said, a good pop-up ad marketing strategy can increase your newsletter sign-up and possibly lead to increased sales.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/use-pop-ads-bolster-jigoshop-ecommerce-business/">Use Pop-Up Ads to Bolster Your  Jigoshop eCommerce Business</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/use-pop-ads-bolster-jigoshop-ecommerce-business/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:75:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Importance of Site Optimization";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}