";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://www.jigoshop.com/?p=45027";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:567:"<p>Introduction Site speed is an important factor to consider with your eCommerce website. Imagine you open you open your web browser to do some online shopping and you stumble upon a went on with this amazing product but the pages <a class="read-more" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/importance-site-optimization/">Read More</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/importance-site-optimization/">Importance of Site Optimization</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Michael Stone";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3748:"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Site speed is an important factor to consider with your eCommerce website.</p>\n<p>Imagine you open you open your web browser to do some online shopping and you stumble upon a went on with this amazing product but the pages take forever to load. The site is basically crawling.</p>\n<p>What would you do?</p>\n<p>Would you stay and become increasingly frustrated as you trudge through your shopping experience? Or, would you take off to another shop?</p>\n<p>Well, the studies are in!</p>\n<p>According to <a style="font-family: Georgia, serif; line-height: 1.5;" href="https://blog.kissmetrics.com/loading-time/?wide=1">surveys compiled by gomez.com and akamai.com</a>, 40% of shoppers will leave your site if the page takes more than 3 seconds to load. Further, these surveys found that 79% of shoppers who are dissatisfied will never return.</p>\n<p>Those are pretty intense statistics. Let&#8217;s see what you can do to not struggle with poor site performance.<span id="more-45027"></span></p>\n<h2>What Can Improve WordPress Optimization?</h2>\n<p>There are several things that can improve a WordPress site and more specifically, your Jigoshop eCommerce site</p>\n<h3>WordPress Hosting</h3>\n<p>When choosing a web host it is important to choose one that is fine tuned to handle WordPress. Usually, a shared hosting plan is built with WordPress in mind because WordPress is so popular and it is generally the go-to for small business and small businesses are also more likely to opt of for a shared hosting plan.</p>\n<p>Usually, a shared hosting plan is built with WordPress in mind because WordPress is so popular and it is generally the go-to for small business and small businesses are also more likely to opt of for a shared hosting plan.</p>\n<p>Even better than a shared hosting plan is a managed WordPress hosting service. These hosts manage a lot of the technical aspects of WordPress hosting for you. Things such as maintaining backups, handling WordPress updates, and even security.</p>\n<h3>Caching</h3>\n<p>The next big help to improving WordPress optimization is the implementation of a caching plugin. The nature of WordPress is that its pages are dynamic, meaning that the pages are built every time the particular page is loaded. Serving dynamic pages can be very taxing on a server and lead to increased load times.</p>\n<p>Caching is the answer to this. In short, instead of generating the web page every time that it is requested, a caching plugin goes through and produces a copy of a page after its&#8217; first time being served.</p>\n<h3>Image Optimization</h3>\n<p>Images are usually the most crippling aspect of a web pages load time. As such, it is important that a picture is optimized for quick load times.</p>\n<p>Images can be reduced in size if they are saved in proper image formats and compression.</p>\n<p>JPEG and PNG are the most popular image formats for the web.</p>\n<p>JPEG is used for images that contain a lot of colors.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, a PNG is used when the image has few colors or when there is a need for transparency.</p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Websites have a lot of components and because of this can take time load. Unfortunately, the longer a site takes to load the less likely a visitor is to stay long enough to view the content.</p>\n<p>There are many ways other than picking good WordPress hosting, using a caching plugin, and optimizing images, to optimize a WordPress site. These three are just the ones that we felt were the most important.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/importance-site-optimization/">Importance of Site Optimization</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.jigoshop.com">Jigoshop</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://www.jigoshop.com/blog/post/importance-site-optimization/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1